					<head>Commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>The commentary of Japheth ben Ali ha-Levi on the book of Job, chapters 23-42.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jrb">Hebrew, Judeo-Arabic</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="150v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Iyov</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש איוב</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="en">Japheth ben Ali, ha-Levi,‏ active 10th century </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="he">יפת בן עלי, הלוי</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>The pointed Hebrew text, accompanied by a verse by verse Arabic translation, is embodied.</p>
								<p>Of the Hebrew text the following parts are preserved: 23:1-24:4, 25:3-5, 27:16-28:18, 29:1-11, 29:15-32:13, 32:20-36:22, 36:26-37:11, 37:18-38:7, 38:16-34, 38:38-39:8, 39:19-41:2, 41:5-42:7, 42:9-17.</p>
								<p>Has a scribal subscription at the beginning.</p>
								<p>Masoretic division into sections and קרי are marked in the margins.</p>
								<p>The numbers of the chapters of the printed text have been added by a later hand.</p>
							</note>
							<incipit xml:lang="he">שרח אלנצף אלתאני מן שרח איוב ללמעלם אבו עלי אלבצרי ר'י'ת'.<locus n="1r"/>
							</incipit>
							<incipit xml:lang="he">בשם יוי אל עולם תפסיר אלנצף אלתאני מן שרח ספר איוב.<locus n="1v"/>
							</incipit>
							<filiation>The handwriting is similar to that of Or 2399, Or 2461, Or 2465 part 1, Or 2466 folios 84-120.</filiation>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent>150 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>180</height>
										<width>136</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>125</height>
										<width>90</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>150 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>18 quires (nos. 1-2, 4-19), originally of 10 leaves each (except the 18th which has 11 leaves). </p>
									<p>Apart from the quires 6-8, 11-12, 17, all the quires are imperfect. </p>
									<p>The quires are signed with Hebrew letters and Arabic words on the upper margin of the first page. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Lacunae after folios: 7, 8, 16, 22, 53, 71, 91, 99, 107, 115, 119, 133, 143. </p>
									<p>Many folios stained or water-damaged. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="14" writtenLines="14">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>The numbers of the chapters have been added by a later hand.</p>
									<p>Separate title page (folio 1r). </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Oriental square and semi-cursive script of the 15th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 150v contains a geneology of the previous owner and a rhyme.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Avraham ben Shelomoh ben Shemu᾿el ben Eliyahu ben Aharon ben Yitsḥaḳ ben Eliyahu Firuz</name>: inscribed in a note, folio 1r . </p>
							<p>An entry recording the name and genealogy of the same owner is also found on folio 150v.</p>
						</additions>
